examples.en: The bad news darkened his mood.
The sky darkened and it started to rain.
The room darkened as a cloud hid the sun's rays.
Tom's face darkened and he turned angrily on Sam.
The building was darkened except for a single light burning in a third-story window.
A power failure temporarily darkened the town.
The last days of her life were darkened by illness.
A poem in which a medieval knight encounters a mysterious beauty in a darkened delve.
